review_blob: This is not a bad beer. It tastes like a water down version of a belgium white beer. For the money I would go with the Saranac Hefewiezen over this.

I love this beer. It has a great aroma that does not overpower the flavor of the beer. It's has a great flavor that does not linger in the mouth. Over all this is the beer I want to drink when I get home from work.
For the money, I like this beer. It has a nice bannana aroma and more flavor than the Blue Moon Belgium Wheat. However, it is not anything like a traditional Belgium wheat.
